				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$k{-}\omega $$\end{document} diagram to simply display the spatial wavenumbers and temporal frequencies of interest, although this comes at the price of discarding information that may be important within the remainder of the frequency space. Alternatively, it is possible to use log–log axes for the k-ω\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
