				\begin{document}$$m=1$$\end{document} (kink) wave perturbations, respectively, to the equilibrium flux tube. The sausage wave (middle) is characterized by an axi-symmetric contraction and expansion of the tube’s cross-section. This produces a periodic compression/rarefaction of both the plasma and magnetic field. The kink wave (right) causes a transverse displacement of the flux tube. In contrast to the sausage wave, the kink wave displacement/velocity field is not axi-symmetric about the flux tube axis. The red lines show the perturbed flux tube boundary and thick arrows show the corresponding displacement vectors. The thin arrows labelled B show the direction of the background magnetic field.
