Studying sausage modes in numerous pore data sets obtained with ROSA, Keys et al. (2018) were able to identify signatures of surface and body waves associated with the oscillating pores. Surface and body modes can be identified by the spatial distribution of the amplitude across the flux tube (Rae and Roberts 1983; Erdélyi and Fedun 2010). For surface modes, all perturbations have a maximum at the tube boundary and will be zero at the center of the tube. For body modes, the kinetic gas pressure, vz\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
