Transverse kink waves have also been studied in small-scale structures in sunspots. Pietarila et al. (2011) identified kink waves in dynamic fibrils (in the immediate vicinity of a sunspot; from Ca ii 8542 Å observations with SST) with periods of ≈135\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
